ty minstrels. Featured in music by the greatest Baroque composers, including Bach and Handel, in the twentieth century it played a vital role in the Early Music Revival and achieved international popularity and notoriety in mass education. Overall, Lasocki and Ehrlich make a case for the recorder being surprisingly present, and significant, throughout Western music history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aRecorder (Musical instrument)xHistory. 7aMUSIC / History & Criticism.2bisacsh1 aEhrlich, Robert, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aEhrlich, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLasocki, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPetri, Michala, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aTarasov, Nikolaj, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aTarasov, Nikolaj, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023 Englishz978311131909408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023z978311131812708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311074978640uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300270648?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300270648423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300270648/original  a978-3-11-074978-6  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131812-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area